title: Timucuan Ecological & Historic Preserve: History of Kingsley Plantation
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     History & Culture     Places     Kingsley Plantation     History of Kingsley Plantation                  History of Kingsley Plantation      During Floridaâ€™s plantation period (1763-1865), Fort George Island was owned by many planters. The site name comes from one of those owners, Zephaniah Kingsley. The Kingsleys lived here from 1814 to 1837.
